⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Oscar Gordon
node H1 · H1 · ⟦Oscar Gordon:H1:9b9cc3⟧

WHO   — Evelyn Cyril "Easy"/Oscar Gordon, an American veteran fresh out of a Southeast Asian war, answering a newspaper ad for "a HERO" — and finding it was meant for him.
WHAT  — A sword-swinging adventurer pulled across worlds to steal the Egg of the Phoenix for Star, the Empress of the Twenty Universes — and to learn that the glory road has no end at the castle gate.
WHERE — From Earth to the dueling-grounds of Nevia, through the shifting Twenty Universes, to the imperial seat of Center — and back out the door again.
WHY   — Because a man wants the quest more than the prize; because heroism is easy and afterward is hard; because what do you do once you have already saved everything?
HOW   — With a blade, blunt courage, and Rufo at his side — then by marrying the Empress, discovering retirement is the cruelest dragon, and riding out for the next adventure.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  The hero's reward is not the throne — it is the next door, and the nerve to walk through it.

